<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-04-30T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-04-30T06:00:00-05:00" n="785" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d785">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Commission/192: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting
                                    Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-04-30T19:00:00+08:00">April 30, 1932—7
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 30—7:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>487. Following from American Consul General at Mukden: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“April 30, 10 a.m. League Commission of Inquiry will leave Mukden
                                        <pb facs="0842" n="738" xml:id="pg_738"/> Monday
                                        morning<note n="7" xml:id="d785fn7">May 2.</note> for
                                    Changchun and North Manchuria, accompanied by <persName corresp="#p_KVKW1">Wellington Koo</persName> and the reduced
                                    Chinese staff.”</p></quote></p>
                        <closer>For the Minister:<lb/><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>